		<div class="postbody">
			
			<h3 >
								<a href="#p52724">Re: What happens when you die?</a>
			</h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=52724&amp;sid=93c2f1de87454fdfd5bcbfe6bf6c938e#p52724"><img src="./styles/Carbon/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>			by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=42716&amp;sid=93c2f1de87454fdfd5bcbfe6bf6c938e">Kwing</a></strong> on Sun Jan 23, 2011 7:52 pm			<br />([msg=52724]see Re: What happens when you die?[/msg])
			</p>

			
			<div class="content">Pardon all the people that'll laugh at me, but I think our souls decompose same as our bodies. Small unintelligent entities feed on us and bits of us decompose, while other bits (spiritual 'bones') may remain intact, especially bits that carry a strong emotional charge which keeps it in place (entire memories may remain intact). If fully formed memories make it into a being that can interpret thought and memory, they think of those memories as past lives. Although some deaths can result in a fully intact entity being tethered to their body or place of death. If their emotional energy is strong enough and restless, you might have a ghost.</div>

			
		</div>

